[{"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The Minister of Finance of the State of North Rhine-Westphalia S-2198 - 3 - V B 2 -bek"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "OFD Cologne S-2198 - 4 - St 114 from 20/03 / 79bek"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "OFD D\u00fcsseldorf S-2198 A - St 11 H from 13/03 / 79S-2198EStK \u00a7 21 EStG A 63ModEnG: 5/3 Modernization and Energy Saving Act - ModEnG - from 27 6 1978; here: monitoring of the prohibition of cumulation according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "Section 5 (3) ModEnG Reference: Decrees of 20 7 1978 of 23 8 1978 and of 27 11 1978 S-2198 - 3 - V B 2; Meeting with Mr. \u00a7 82a EStDV) and 3 expenses for maintenance costs for owner-occupied single-family houses within the meaning of \u00a7 82a Abs 3 EStDV i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "the second regulation amending the EStDV 1977 the promotion of the same measure according to the Modernization and Energy Saving Act (only energy saving program and federal-state program)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "In accordance with Section 13 (7) ModEnG, the owner has to undertake in the relevant cases to repay the subsidies received, provided that he takes advantage of a tax break of the type described above for the same structural measure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "To the extent described, there is a prohibition on cumulation of the types of funding"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the prohibition of cumulation states that this tax advantage excludes the extra-tax incentive, but not the other way around the extra-tax incentive excludes the tax relief"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The tax concessions are to be granted if the conditions specified in the Tax Act are met, even if it is certain that non-tax subsidies have been granted under the ModEnG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The grant granted is then possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "to repay"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The decision as to whether there is an accumulation case is therefore made solely by the licensing authority, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "to be met by the municipality, not by the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "However, this must provide the licensing authority with the necessary factual information so that the licensing authority can make its decision"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "II For this purpose, proceed as follows: 1 The licensing authorities send the tax offices that are responsible for the assessment of the respective applicant a copy of the approval notice (decree of 20 7 1978 S-2198 - 3 - V B 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The tax number of the applicant results from this copy of the approval notification, provided that this has already been recorded for tax purposes, since the tax number must be specified in the application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "In the application form, the applicant also declares his consent to the tax office informing the granting authority about the use of a tax advantage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "In the approval notification (model Mod 2) under D (conditions and information) at No. 2 it is expressly stated: \"You have agreed that the tax office may inform the licensing authority about any use of a tax break within the meaning of Section 5 (3) sentence 2 ModEnG or an investment grant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "\"Insofar as the applicants are already listed for tax purposes, the copies of the approval notices must be included in the tax files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, they are to be stored in the tax office in a central alphabetical order"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "2 If, in individual cases, an application is made for a tax break of the type mentioned in Section 5 (3) ModEnG, this must be granted, provided that the tax law requirements are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "If, in such a case, based on the copy of the approval notification, the taxpayer has been granted a subsidy, the granting authority must be informed with reference to the file number of this authority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The facts brought forward by the taxpayer and the tax benefit to be granted must be reported, whereby it is sufficient to make a statement as to whether the benefit falls under Section 5 (3) sentence 2 ModEnG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The preparation of a form for the notification to the granting authority is to be refrained from for the time being, since it can be assumed that the number of relevant cases is likely to be very low in view of the clear prohibition of cumulation and the control procedure known to the beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the tax office (sub-district) has to check in those cases in which a benefit of the above-mentioned type is claimed whether a copy of a notification of approval is available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "This will be in the V files, if any"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The first time an assessment is made, it must be checked whether a notification of approval has been filed centrally"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "If the tax return is processed at the transfer point, a submission to the APSt is required anyway if deductions for wear and tear, increased deductions and special depreciation for buildings are noticeably claimed for the first time (reference to the flowchart for subject 2 part 2 page 10 ALDA Fest No. 15 06)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The APSt must therefore proceed in the same way as the subdistrict (see above)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "III On the question of the amount of tax relief in the case of a grant that has already been granted, which may then"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "I refer to the new version of section 163 of the income tax guidelines based on the income tax supplement guidelines 1978. According to the income tax return forms for 1978 (Appendix V, lines 15 and 55, Appendix GSE, lines 25 and 52), the taxpayer must declare whether grants have been granted in accordance with the ModEnG in the assessment year have been"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "If such subsidies were granted during the assessment period, the transfer from the takeover point to the APSt must also be made if increased deductions and special depreciation for buildings are not claimed for the first time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "The APSt (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "the sub-district) has to check whether there is a notification of approval and, if so, notify the approval authority as described above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "If there are any difficulties in carrying out the above procedure, please report me"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047514.xml"}, "text": "Tax Promotion Act Income tax / wage tax / church tax North Rhine-Westphalia"}]